---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Ghana Business Analysis — Economic Reports, Sector Intelligence, Risk Assessments"
  description="In-depth Ghana business analysis for investors and diaspora founders. Sector rankings, risk alerts, policy tracking, and opportunity scoring. Updated continuously."
  keywords="Ghana economic analysis, Ghana business report, Ghana investment analysis, Ghana sector report 2026, Ghana risk assessment, diaspora investment guide"
>
  <div class="article-header">
    <h1>Ghana Business Analysis</h1>
    <div class="article-meta">
      Evidence-grounded analysis from 40+ intelligence cycles. No hype. No generic Africa-rising narratives.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>Latest Reports</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="card-grid">
      <a href="/analysis/gipc-reform-2026" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
        <span class="card-tag policy">Policy Change</span>
        <h3>GIPC Reform 2026: $200K Minimum Capital Requirement Removed</h3>
        <p>Ghana removes the barrier that locked out diaspora founders with less than $200K. What it means, what risks remain, and what to do now.</p>
        <div class="card-meta"><span>March 2026</span><span>Confidence: MEDIUM</span></div>
      </a>

      <a href="/analysis/cocoa-crisis-2026" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
        <span class="card-tag risk">Risk Alert</span>
        <h3>Cocoa Crisis: Cocobod Debt Quantified at $850M+</h3>
        <p>Farmers unpaid, banks exposed, reform announced but not implemented. Full analysis of Ghana's cocoa sector crisis.</p>
        <div class="card-meta"><span>March 2026</span><span>Confidence: HIGH</span></div>
      </a>

      <a href="/analysis/ghana-gse-crash-2026" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
        <span class="card-tag risk">Risk Alert</span>
        <h3>GSE: +77% Rally Then Crash — What Happened</h3>
        <p>The Ghana Stock Exchange hit 15,000 then lost 875 points in one day. We trace the T-bill compression, equity rotation, and profit-taking cascade.</p>
        <div class="card-meta"><span>March 2026</span><span>Confidence: HIGH</span></div>
      </a>

      <a href="/analysis/oil-palm-opportunity" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
        <span class="card-tag">Opportunity</span>
        <h3>Oil Palm: The $2B Import Substitution Gap</h3>
        <p>Ghana's national oil palm policy targets 100K hectares. Is this a real opportunity or another government agricultural promise?</p>
        <div class="card-meta"><span>March 2026</span><span>Confidence: MEDIUM</span></div>
      </a>

      <a href="/analysis/hormuz-crisis-impact-ghana" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
        <span class="card-tag risk">Global Shock</span>
        <h3>Hormuz Crisis: Oil Price Impact on Ghana's Economy</h3>
        <p>Brent at $108, WTI at $94. How the Hormuz crisis cascades through Ghana's fuel, transport, food, and currency systems.</p>
        <div class="card-meta"><span>March 2026</span><span>Confidence: HIGH</span></div>
      </a>

      <a href="/analysis/imf-exit-2026" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
        <span class="card-tag policy">Policy Change</span>
        <h3>Ghana's IMF Exit: What Comes After the Program Ends</h3>
        <p>IMF exit imminent (April/May 2026). Independent Fiscal Council announced. What the post-IMF institutional framework looks like — and what could go wrong.</p>
        <div class="card-meta"><span>March 2026</span><span>Confidence: HIGH</span></div>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="section-header" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
      <h2>Ghana Macro Dashboard</h2>
      <p>Key indicators tracked across 40+ intelligence cycles. Sources: GSS, BoG, IMF, World Bank.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="stats-bar">
      <div class="stat-card positive"><div class="value">6.0%</div><div class="label">GDP Growth (2025)</div></div>
      <div class="stat-card"><div class="value">3.3%</div><div class="label">Headline CPI (Feb 2026)</div></div>
      <div class="stat-card"><div class="value">14.0%</div><div class="label">BoG Policy Rate</div></div>
      <div class="stat-card"><div class="value">GHS 10.97</div><div class="label">USD/GHS Rate</div></div>
      <div class="stat-card positive"><div class="value">$14.8B</div><div class="label">Gross Reserves</div></div>
      <div class="stat-card"><div class="value">$31.1B</div><div class="label">2025 Exports (+63% YoY)</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
